          <physDesc>
            <p>Vellum, about 8 ¾ in. by 5 1/2, consisting of 148 leaves, a few of which are much stained and torn, especially foll. 41, 42, 76, 147 and 148. The quires are 16 in number, the first and second being imperfect. They are now signed with letters, and the folios have been numbered with Coptic arithmetical figures, up to  (i.e. 148, fol. 146 a). A leaf is wanting at the beginning, and another after fol. 7. There are from 18 to 26 lines in each page.</p>
